reviews.review_text:
Well played show… !  Hey Gang,  I give this one a solid 4 out of 5 stars.  There was a reason GDM released this run on the download series; it's very well played, dare I say it sounds like the GD rehearsed?  This is a good very upfront audience recording with Nak 300's.  It sounds almost like a FM broadcast, or good enough to mix with a soundboard feed.  Again, it sounds digital with no hiss; it does sound a little tinny but it is crispy.  Also,  a nice upload job by Kevin Tobin with all the metadata correctly lining up in your software.  

yes, I downloaded the show because the download series sounds less to be desired; I was disappointed when I played it back through my system.  It sounds compressed almost on the level of a bad MP3, but it's a soundboard.  I believe the reason was bad encoding on the upload; I know the master DAT soundboard doesn't sound that bad… anyway,  so supplement your desire with a good audience tape I say … Great performance and this a good audience source too !
